< text>
I used MailMax for over 3 years. Always helpful & friendly. If you're a couple of days late paying the bill for your mailbox, there ok with it ... just don't go beyond a week or you'll get a late fee. Not open on weekends but in a good location for the South side of town. Not always fun to check your mail in the Summer, but there's a liquor store 2 units to the left to cool you down. Plus there's  a donut shop a few units to the right to get you coffee on. And 2 banks in the same shopping to do your money business with if you need to cash or mail a cashier's check.< /text>

<resp>None< /resp><Rating>4< /Rating><review>My story is a long one, and I specifically waited to write this review until after I had an opportunity to resolve everything with the store.

A good friend of mine recommended Bassett due to the high quality furniture but did warn me that their operations team could probably use a little extra work.

I visited the store back in July after making an appointment online and was impressed with the sales associate Katie who showed my wife and I around discussing the various options to consider when purchasing a sofa.

We decide to have Katie out to the house to have a better idea of what would work for the room.  This was awesome and would have earned a five star review. She brought tons of samples and options for us to look at which really helped us shape the room.  Following this excellent experience we decided to move forward and place an order for a sofa ottoman and rug (around $6k).  Katie did warn us that due to Covid orders are taking a little bit longer than the usual 8 weeks for custom furniture.

This is where my frustrations began. After you sign a contract with Bassett they do not have any processes in place to proactively update you on the status of your order.  As a type a person and with family coming into town I wanted to really understand when my order would arrive.  I repeatedly reached out to the store with limited information.

I don‚Äôt know if you‚Äôve ever seen the dominoes app where you can literally see every single stage of the process of what your order is inputted, being assembled, finished, and out for delivery... Bassett needs this.

After 10 weeks and still not receiving any communication or my order I escalated to the store management, Jared.  I went in guns blazing and was pleasantly surprised with Jared‚Äòs response and effort to get me information on a timely basis.  He was able to provide me with daily updates and personally delivered several of my items in two shipments versus the originally planned one to get me my items as fast as possible.

I went from 5 star to 1 star to finish at 4... I would consider using them again as I love the furniture but they need help in operations.

Ryan<//review><Name>Ryan Granchalek</Name>< user>

< Text>
We bought a ~$2,000 bed from Bassett.  The bed was advertised as 100% solid hardwood--yet large portions of the bed we received are actually made from particle board.

After exchanging several emails with their customer team we learned that Basset does not actually make 100% solid wood beds and that other spec information provided on their website and by their in store sales team was also wrong.

And on top of all of this, the bed also arrived damaged!

As you might expect, we asked Bassett repeatedly to please provide us the bed that we ordered (or a refund), but they refused.  Absolutely ridiculous.

Update:  here we are over a month later, and still no refund.  They still continue to claim to make solid wood beds on their website, even though they've admitted in emails repeatedly that large portions of those beds are actually particle board.</Text>

<Text>Shopping with Bassett furniture was our worst mistake!!  One month ago we went into their Roseville California store.  We were told all their furniture is made in America with the finest quality material.  Their sales rep repeated this over and over again.  She showed us a couch that was being discontinued. After an hour being in the store...we purchased a leather sofa that was on clearance.  There were 2 of these couches in New York.  She explained it would be a 4 to 6 week delivery.  Two weeks later, our couch arrives.  The delivery men bring the couch into the living room and take the plastic cover off.  A tag is on the couch states...MADE IN CHINA!!!!!!!!  Can you imagine seeing that tag?  MADE IN CHINA.  I WAITED 2 weeks so I could calmed down before I contacted the store.  I emailed the sales rep and spoke with the manager.  The manager said the leather is not the high quality standard leather, but the frame was made here and sent to China to finish the product. < review>
15 years ago I found this Vet when my cat was very sick.  Dr Salwan was amazing, kind and helped me through a cancer diagnosis and treatment.  Never had any issues with the staff, etc.  Years later, my other cat came down with the same cancer and Dr Salwan was again, very helpful and compassionate.

Fast forward to now and the story is VASTLY different.  I called last Sunday to get help for my 1.5yr cat who hadn't used the litter box is a few days and was vomiting liquid (he is known to try to eat anything he can find, just like a puppy).  They could not see him.  Not only that but the girl on the other end of the line was rude and dismissive.  What a horrible way to treat someone who has a sick animal.  I ended up taking kitty to Beacon for emergency service.  They were compassionate, responsive and helpful.  Bloodwork, x-rays, fluids......unfortunately no diagnosis was found.

Follow up today with his regular vet and we saw Dr Salwan.  I was hopeful for the same good service I'd once had.  I left kitty for x-rays and expected a call back to discuss next step.  3 hrs later I called to check, the answer was simply "you can come pick him up now".  Wait, what?  What's wrong with him?  How are we going to fix it?  Nobody has contacted me.  I am then told oh sorry, x-ray results take 1-2 days, doctor will talk to you then.  I'm sorry but the cat is not eating, is dehydrated and has not had a bowel movement in a week.  I am absolutely disgusted with this service.  This is a life we are talking about, a member of my family.  I have now spent $1600 and my cat is still very sick with no path forward.  This is unacceptable.  What has happened to this place?

Additionally, I neglected to comment on the fact that I had a similar incident in August with my 9yo cat.  Took days to get results from his x-rays.  Many phone calls, thankfully, his was a minor issue and was resolved easily.......luckily.

Dr Salwan is a good Vet, WHEN he is onsite.  Seems he doesn't work there much anymore and the staff is overworked and frustrated.  This may be an OK place if you need simple things like vaccinations or a simply check-up.  But for Gods sake, don't bring your animal here if it is ill, who knows how long it will take to get them checked IF they can even see you when you need to be seen.

First time I've ever written a review..... I hope this helps prevent the anxiety and needless cost that I 've had.....and still with no fix for my sweet little cat.

Update : 4 days later, Dr still hasn't called to talk to me about the results.< /review>

<Text>GREAT ... service, doctors, and prices !

The doctors know what they're doing, if you provide good details of the conditions your pet is experiencing, they're good at getting to the root cause, and properly addressing the issue.

If you just show up, they want to do a round of diagnostics as a baseline to work with, which makes complete sense.

i had a dog who got a a large splinter embedded under their skin that the doctor at first thought was a possible tumor, so he wanted to do more investigation.

i asked him to cut the splinter out, which generated a concern on his part that i was asking him to cut open my dog even though he didn't know what was in there.

that is a very healthy response from the doctor, but i'd witnessed it happening and knew it was a wood splinter, so i very much appreciated his trust in me as the owner to do the surgery.

and he removed the sticker, and makita is all better now !

the concern on the doctor's part, as well as his flexibility on saving on testing to check for a tumor reflect great service in terms of trying to please a pet owner.

thank you for the great service, jeff</Text>< Pics>

< Review>
I'm only giving one star, because I have to, but if I had a choice, I would give none.

I brought my 4 month old teacup puppy in after he was showing signs of being wobbly, tired and completely out of it. The doctor, a heavy set Indian man (he never told us his name) came in with zero emotion and did an "exam" on our puppy. His exam consisted of checking his heart beat, his gums and pressing in certain areas of his body; no temperature check and no ear check, which is a pretty common practice when performing a physical exam on any animal.

He then suggested $600 worth of blood tests, x-rays and medications. However, we can't afford that so we opted out of the blood tests and x-rays and just got the medications. He told us our pup would receive a shot to help rehydrate his body and another that would be an antibiotic. However, later in the evening when we were looking up the side effects of the medication he was given since he was showing weakness and pain in his sides and back, we found out it wasn't an antibiotic at all. It was instead an antiemetic which is to help stop vomiting (which wasn't a major concern when we brought him in).

While we were waiting for his shots to be done, a man came in saying that he had called CHP about a cat being hit by a car and was told they brought the cat here...He asked about the cat's well being and they said the cat was very aggressive, and would be sent to the SPCA where they would probably not adopt it out and then put it down. The man wanted to adopt the cat to save it from such a fate, and the same doctor who saw us, tried to talk him out of it. I couldn't believe it!

Do NOT take your pet here ever. They don't care about your animals, they care about their checks. All those "Google User" reviews are fake reviews from the company itself trying to praise themselves so that suckers like us come in. They are absolutely insincere, lack compassion, and really only want as much money as they can get from you...and my dog isn't even better.<//Review>

< Review>
I first brought my Pup into Tricity, May 2015. Dr. Salwan and the other staff doctors treated her with cutting-edge technology. Doctor Raj is the reason my aunt's RABBIT DIED!

When taking the rabbit (Neffy) in for a simple checkup checkup DR Raj Salwan recommended an x-ray. He never brought up the risk of the x-ray or informed us Neffy would be put to sleep for it. After picking Neffy up she was really drugged up. Raj said that she was okay there was noting to be worried about she just had a hair ball and water and pineapple juice would fix it. They diagnosis also clearly stated that Gastris Stasis was RULED OUT. Later that day around 8 Neffy was not looking good at all. She seemed like she was in pain and couldn't really move. My sister was so worried she called the vet. A receptionist spoke to Raj and told us that everything was fine (not to worry) and that it could take about 24 hours before she's okay. They also mentioned that they have her more of a dosage because she was a bigger rabbit (she's a dwarf rabbit). My sister asked are you sure because she doesn't look good and I don't want her to die in the middle of the night. Again the receptionist said not to worry she just had a hairball and the drugs will ware off.

Neffy died that night. A very slow uncomfortable death.

To make matters worse we were never able to get a hold of Raj despite making appointments with him and coming in 6 and calling countless more. Someone at the office thought it was better to inform us that Neffy died because of Gastris Stasis and that it was a very serious issue they couldn't do anything about. But remember when it was RULED OUT. Tri city Veterinary Hospital diagnosed Neffy after she died and began hiding information (such as what she was drugged with and x rays) so we couldn't determine what actually killed her.

Neffy was my aunt's rabbit. After an accident that took away her ability to walk she went through depression. It was recommends that she get a pet to overcome this. That's where Neffy entered our family. My aunt now blames herself because if she just went to a different vet or not taken Neffy in at all She would still be alive.

I don't think I could sleep at night knowing this could happen to someone else's pet.
The least Tri city Veterinary Hospital could do is make a change. To not take on an animal they don't know how to care for. To use the correct amount of dosage. To understand that a life is in their hands and decisions have terrible consequence to others.<//Text>

<time>1438301732960</time><Rate>4<//Rate><text>Boy, it seems like the "panties in a bunch" crowd is out in force. This little church serves a predominantly Filipino and Mexican population. VERY warm and humid, so get a seat near a door and bring a hand fan.  Lots of Mass times, unbelievable confession opportunities, A poor parish run by an order not the diocese, but still,  a nice place to spend an hour or so a couple times a week.

Where to begin to counter the distortions? Maybe with, what have you done to enrich the community? Are you just  there, notebook in hand, to jot down the slights and GIRM failures. If the latter, I suggest you take your notebook to Queen of Angels and see if the guys in charge of the diocese do a better job. Hint, no, the lapses are legend, so you might want to take that up with his excellency. Attire? You're sniping because their attire is TOO nice? Is this a joke? One can only wonder how you must present yourself.  Dunderhead sermons? Perhaps not all in the pews all are biblical and liturgical scholars of your caliber, so the priests feel the need to speak to the faithful present. Regarding the light in the Adoration Chapel. Here's an idea. Contact the office about buying a suitable red hanging lamp. Make payments. Put your money where your outrage is. Oh, before you say they declined your offer, please understand if you do, I'll check.

As for the other poster. With due respect, are you a parishioner or just a nice person hoping to get donations. If the former, I refer you to my initial question. What have you done? Are you a Knight, greeter, usher, volunteer of any sort? I did the cancer dance a few years back, so I appreciate your limitations, but please, appreciate the time limitations of others. BTW, it's a hokey little carnival, but it's been going on at the same time for decades. I believe Hueneme days is a veritable neophyte at 15 years.

I started coming to Star of the Sea a couple of years ago, just for a change.  I was kind of the ugly girl at the prom--no dance invitations. When the fiesta came about in August, I volunteered and donated. Guess what? I was on my way. I met a few people then a few more, and we all laugh at our communication failures. As a summer area resident,  I also attend Santa Cruz and Mary Magdalene Church and Chapel. I must admit some partiality to the Camarillo church as it is air conditioned, but the Latin Mass at the Chapel is majestic and should be experienced by the orthodox.<//text><pictures>None</pictures><Resp>None< /Resp>< GmapID>

1459650961478<//date>
< Rating>
3</Rating>
<Name>Priscilla M Gray< /Name>< text>
I have been going to this church for more than four years as I live within its parish boundaries. It is run by the Augustinian Recollects who have a beautiful mother house adjoining the parish campus. There is much "new age" intrusion in this parish such as: prevalence of the orans posture by the faithful which is not corrected by the priests, insipid hymn music, an incomplete artsy broken crucifix above the altar, the Tabernacle of our Lord is in an adjoining room and it is a pathetic-looking box which is not properly elevated away from pawing hands. The sanctuary light is not red. The adoration room does not even offer a Cross for the Corpus of our Lord. "Eucharistic ministers" are mostly women who often appear to feel excessive pride in their self importance. They wear shoes which they teeter on while carrying the Body and Blood of our Lord. They do not treat our Lord with proper decorum. (One exception I have noticed are the Extraordinary Ministers of the Eucharist in the evening Spanish Mass) Sometimes the priests in a hurry to "get through quickly" distributing Holy Communion while they take up an inordinate amount of time on simplistic sermons which do not explain the readings in the Holy Mass or the teachings of our Catholic church. There is much applause the faithful toward the end of the Liturgy before the Final Blessing. The applause usually has to do with praying for vocations. My teenage son, whom some priest friends think has a priestly vocation, hates going to the Masses at St Mary's for all the above reasons so we spend gasoline money to travel to other churches to get something that feels like a Holy Catholic ritual rather than a new age feel-good self congratulatory pat-on-the-back. Santa Clara is a little better. I hear the chapel at Santa Clara is more "solid". If you want to experience the standard of a Catholic ritual that includes the liturgical music which the Church recommends then take a trip to Thomas Aquinas College chapel in Santa Paula or assist at the Tridentine Mass at St Mary Magdalen Chapel in Camarillo. The Augustinians at Mary, Star of the Sea are kind in the confessional. The lines are often a very long wait and you must stand while you wait. If you cannot stand for a half hour then i recommend confession at Our Lady of Guadalupe where they organize sitting in the pews while you wait to have your confession heard. The Augustinians are desperate for new vocations but they have not learned that young men and women yearn for truth and high standards, not new age, feelgood stroking and the truly devout men will choose the Norbertines if they want to join an order.  We have experienced the Body of our Lord being treated with lukewarmness or even disrespect at Mary Star of the Sea. It is a good place to go for the sacrament of Confession. The priests are gentle.< /text>

I used to love this place. It was a favorite, we used to drive almost 2 hours to come back here. Not anymore. Last time we visited was October Saturday 14, 2017. The food was aweful, it had a taste of either starting to rot, having it too long in a fridge that I'm certain doesn't work well or just a bad cook...which I don't want to blame. But they shouldn't serve food that's not good anymore. We all got sick that very night. We all tried each other's food, most of it was seafood (Which we enjoy) and we all agreed it didn't taste good. I'm so upset about this because they used to be so great, I'm not sure what changed but I'm sad to say goodbye. I hope they fix or change whatever is wrong. Wish all the best.< /review>

<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
Best dive bar around. This bar has been here a very long time. A must stop on the way to or from Las Vegas or just to go have a beer any day of the week. It‚Äôs off old route 66 that runs along the 15 fwy. Pool table, juke box and nice big patio.  Live music on the weekends. They put on great events as well. Bike days and nights. Under new management/ownership so it‚Äôs now called Screaming Sally‚Äôs (sister bar of Mustang Sally‚Äôs in Rancho). Place has been cleaned up nicely. Stop by and check it out.<//review>

< text>
Yes, it is a full-on biker bar...but don't let that stop you for visiting!  I am from south OC, father of two, average "Joe" and EVERYONE in the place treated me with the utmost respect.  Bartenders were absolutely AWESOME - great service and fantastic attitudes.  And it was a Tuesday!  We met the owner who gave me and my friends a tour and the patrons (yes, a few just out of the joint) could not have been nicer to me.  I also learned all about the fundraising the local "clubs" sponsor thru activities at the bar.  Seriously, if you miss out on this place - well, more beer for me...oh, and you're an idiot.< /text>

I totally get why people would be annoyed with this. However considering how many millions of people are going through this right now, it's going to be rough going no matter how good, how well prepared the call center is given the numbers of unemployed.

< review>
Pretty good quality cuts of fish in my opinion. Pricing is not too bad as well and they have a pretty decent presentation.

The Kamon Sashimi and Kamon lover is actually pretty generous and we definitely ordered too much for a group of 4 people. Everything in the menu just looked so good! I'd say probably 2-3 of the set items would have been enough but we orders 4 things and smaller plates of oysters sashimi.

They also give you complimentary little bowls of squash soup that were surprisingly very delicious.

Service is very fast and efficient and the place is decently sized. Make a reservation if you can because it can get pretty busy.< /review>

<user_id>104933877977895801614<//user_id><Gmap_id>0x80c32a7c9d6a02b3:0xc35f37ecb6692f07</Gmap_id>< Review>
Uncommonly fresh and delicious. Kamon, is one of the very few establishments that offer chu-toro; this cut of tuna is still fatty but not as fatty as o-toro. They also have kizami wasabi, a fresh chopped wasabi that‚Äôs been marinated in soy sauce. It‚Äôs enjoyed by placing it on top of your sashimi and if you must, lightly dipping into soy sauce. Every order is presented in a way that satisfies the eyes as much as it does your palate. Freshness and attention to detail are both defining traits of successful restaurants that can be seen and tasted. Of course service was stellar, servers, most notably Steven, came to check up just enough to make you feel attended to and not forgotten. Part of the management is a young gentleman, Kevin. Who is as professional as he is kind. Observing the restaurant dynamic as the dinner rush steadily picked up, he was sure to be everywhere at once with grace and a sense of calm. From welcoming and seating patrons, assisting servers, delivering orders, and checking in on the back of the house. Kamon, fresh clean and delicious.< /Review>

< Review>
I would consider this place as a typical Japanese restaurant, with sushi, bento boxes, and rolls as your main options. The food tastes great and seems to be fresh. The pumpkin soup served at the beginning of the meal is nice. The service and ambiance is up to par. My only criticism of the food is that some dishes can be overly salty. I drank many glasses of water during and after my meal.

Overall, a solid choice for Japanese food, but nothing particularly outstanding.</Review>

<GmapID>0x80c32a7c9d6a02b3:0xc35f37ecb6692f07<//GmapID><text>We used to like this place in the past.  After we moved farther from this side of the town, we stopped going there.  Either our tastes have changed or their food prep has changed, but this time around, the food wasn't as great as it was before.

We ordered Oyako Don, Bento (chicken), and a sushi boat deluxe.  The oyako don was normal like other places.  However, the bento was not as good.  It's been my experience that over here, the meat is almost overcooked and burned (beef or chicken).  This of course makes the meat dry and chewey, especially for the beef.  If you want to know a place that cooks great meat for a bento, try Daifuku in Diamond Bar.

The miso soup was a bit too salty for my taste, but I understand that's based on personal preference.  I've been to other restaurants where the miso was prepared very well.

One change I do not like is the fact that they no longer allow you to make reservations on weekends for any times after 6:30pm.  They used to let you do it, but I assume that caused issues for them.  Rather than just not take reservation, I personally think they should just charge a reservation fee for those who really need to make a reservation (ie. when you have kids with you and you can't afford to wait 30-50 minute).</text>< Rating>
3< /Rating>

<Name>Pauline Cao<//Name><pictures>None<//pictures><gmap_id>0x80c32a7c9d6a02b3:0xc35f37ecb6692f07</gmap_id>< resp>

<rating>2<//rating><user_id>104037025158193807511</user_id>< Review>
What I Ordered
- Tempura Zaru Soba
- Salmon Roll

After a long day at work, sitting through traffic, we finally arrived at Kamon. My first thoughts when we walked in, "This place smells weird....in a bad way... ew." After awhile, I guess I got used to the smell -_-. We were seated at the sushi bar because we were too hungry to wait for a table.

I'm not sure how we were suppose to order there but, no one gave us a menu for a good 10 minutes I had to flag a waiter down for one. I guess we are suppose to order sushi from the sushi chefs and regular items on the menu through the waiter? However, there is not list of sushi options because their specials on the wall!!! How am I suppose to know what they have or not? What if I wanted a roll instead of sashimi?! -_-

I ordering a Salmon Roll from the sushi chef. All he said was, "With or without veggies?" -_- It was pretty basic to me. Nothing special. The Tempura Zaru Soba gave me how. Only to my dismay, it was also, mediocre. The soba had no flavor. The dipping sauce was okay but, it couldn't save the soba. The tempura was standard. I don't know why my friend likes it here so much.. I will not be back. :(</Review>

< Text>
Great quite atmosphere.  Smaller villas with limited rims in each, helps keep the nose down.  A little more difficult to find your room, but we liked it much better than the typical hotel.  Have to pay extra for parking, but maybe able to ask for a discount or maybe a couple of free breakfast vouchers.  Buffet breakfast is awesome and everything was fresh with great variety, but way too expensive at around $20. Overall we highly recommend this place, one of our favorites in the area, rooms are on the higher end of the price scale< /Text>

< text>
After nearly two weeks of traveling and staying in hotels that didn't live up to their ratings I knew that my trip would end on an upbeat because I was going to be at Hotel Karlan.  Family members, who live in Stockholm, choose the Karlin for their San Diego vacation every July.

It exceeded my high expectations.  The staff, the luxurious rooms, the spacious grounds, and the moderate rates all come together to make guests feel welcome and cared for.  On the road, the best I can usually hope for is a clean bathroom and a comfortable bed.  The Karlan bathrooms literally sparkle and the comfortable beds are enhanced by quality linen.

The location allows vacationers to avoid the crush of city traffic and is convenient to some top restaurants in North San Diego County.< /text>

< gmapID>
0x80dbf9fcd5c745d1:0xbc0f76cc80873c38< /gmapID>
<pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOgRubTaRPGA9bl39NEvHmLvIOhHHSKe5X0bvJf=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNRwfBz_sLpGmWM2-qDLPPQvVr0xKVVb4FNujDu=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics>< Review>
Looking for a delightfully loud, inconvenient, and dated room? Look no further than the Hotel Karlan by Hilton.

Listen, I actually prefer to stay at all Hilton Hotels over Marriott, and was looking forward to this "resort-like" retreat at a 4-star hotel to begin my honeymoon. My experience was far from resort-like, however, and I felt as though I would have been better off staying in a local City Motel with a blinking vacancy sign off a freeway somewhere (no offense if that's where you choose to stay).

Be forewarned first and foremost, you will need to carry your luggage up or down stairs (see pictures) depending where your room is. Although the front desk politely pointed me toward the elevator, what he failed to mention, is that my room (#325) was located across the complex down a set of stairs, where I had to scamper down a flight of stairs with four suit cases (wife included) without managing to topple over myself. Despite being extremely aggravated about the lack of heads up, I went about my evening.

The issues didn't stop there, unfortunately. Here are some other negatives with the hotel, besides being separated and inconvenient to access:
+ Gaps in the doors cause noise to flow right through to the room
+ The sliding door in the bathroom could prove it easier to move 14 cinder blocks than actually open the door
+ Shower door slams behind you--careful not to let it smack you on the way in
+ In the year 2018, we all have electronic devices (phones, tablets, watches, laptops), and in my business travels, I expect there to be plenty of outlets and if possible, USB plugs. This hotel has neither, with each device being a treasure hunt to find plugs hidden behind the bed, and no USB-accessible outlets.

Overall, this was an extremely disappointing start to our honeymoon vacation. I explained these issues to the front desk, and their compensation was to provide a free breakfast. Albeit helpful, it didn't solve the numerous issues and unpleasurable experience we had, so we decided to check out early move elsewhere.</Review>

< text>
Hotel Karlan was both a five star and a two star hotel all in one. The reason for the five star was because the restaurant and room service was superb and the accommodations were nice the workout room was functional and my husband genuinely enjoyed the hot tub and pool with the cabanas. <Time>1540401562881< /Time>< Text>
I was coming into town for a wedding that started at 5pm. I arrived at 130 pm, but was told that early check was absolutely not available as they were completely booked from the night before. (I thought check out was noon? Was there really nothing they could do?) They were kind enough to let me hang out by the pool while I waited the hour and half out.

The room looked great. The bathroom was updated with a huge glass shower. I have no complaints there. There was no escaping the noise above or people outside. I had a ground level room. There are unavoidable stairs so if you have any restrictions at all make sure you are not on the first level at all.

My biggest issue with Hotel Karlan is that I left with bug bites all over my legs. I have experienced bed bugs in that past and these bites are consistent with what I had then. I will never stay again because of the bed bugs.</Text>

This hotel is a bit unlike the other hotels that I've stayed at while traveling, and I enjoyed the change of experience. The hotel rooms are segmented into multiple connected buildings, kind of like some apartment complexes, with most rooms featuring a front door that leads outside as well as a balcony. This is a big plus because the rooms feel more secluded/private. One notable con: The breakfast is good but overpriced if you don't get vouchers, at $19 for the breakfast buffet at the time I write this.< /Text>

<rate>3</rate><pictures>None<//pictures>< text>
I stayed here for a week and it was fine and okay, but not my best stay due to several little annoyances. First, the a/c in the room doesn't seem to make a lot of sense. No matter what I set the thermostat to, it goes off at random times, albeit sometimes with a louder fan, and the room never seems to get to the temperature I set on the panel. Not sure how else to interpret it, but I would think when I set the thermostat to 70 it means I want the ambient temperature of the room to be 70, but it never felt that cool before the a/c would turn off. Too make up for this lack of cool, the mini fridge was actually a freezer, apparently. I was here for several days, so I stocked up on snacks and beverages, and they all froze, including the carbonated cans that burst... No knob to adjust the temperature seems to exist anywhere on the fridge unit. I even got so desperate as to look up the owners manual and it looks like there should be a knob on the inner ceiling that simply doesn't exist on this hotel model. Others that I traveled here with that were in other rooms were having similar freezing problems. Also, my bed had no top sheet, just a fitted sheet and a comforter, which is weird. I figured housekeeping would notice and fix it, and to be honest I was too lazy at the end of each day to contact anyone about it, but never got fixed for the whole week. Otherwise it was clean and quiet, at least in my building (7A) and was fine, although discovering all the little quirks over an entire week kind of wore me out on the place.<//text>

<Review>This place is gorgeous with amazing and serene views. It does not feel like a hotel, but more like a retreat. Our room was huge compared to other hotels I've stayed in, and the bathroom was well lit and accommodating. We had a courtyard room which offered a patio with table and chairs as well as a ceiling fan. It was private enough that we could set out there and really enjoy the relaxing view of open space, and our children had a place to play so they didn't feel cooped up all the time. This hotel is also conveniently located to shopping areas, lots of restaurants, and every destination we had planned to go to on our trip to San Diego. The pool is heated which was especially nice. There was also a hot tub, and both the pool and hot tub were clean and well taken care of. Large soft towels were also provided poolside as well as nice cabana style areas located around the pool. Room service, a gym, and office area also available. The staff were all so nice and went above and beyond to make sure our stay was well enjoyed. The place is on the pricier side, but well worth it to us. Although, we did find it odd that for as nice of a place as it is, and with how much money we were spending each night to stay there, we still had to pay for wifi! Other than that, we would not only recommend this place to everyone we know, we would also stay here again and again whenever we visit San Diego :-)< /Review>< Rating>

< Text>
I was here for meetings. My first experience  what's not good at this property. They had a 3 pm check-in but we're not able  able to check in until 5 p.m. They did not update us at all while we waited. The rooms here are nice a large. The bed and pillows are exactly how I like them. Also the bathrooms have recently being done over and are quite large.  We ate breakfast  at the asada Grill and the Black Horse Pub for lunch and dinner. The food at the Asado Grill and at the Black Horse Pub was very good. We did a side dinner in the Asada grill for our group and the food was excellent as well as the service. The hotel has a large pool and large Cabana areas. The hotel is set up like a large complex with different buildings. It can be a walk from the front desk if you are in the back in the 600 building. All in all the property was nice and I would stay there again.< /Text>

<date>1372143075291</date><Rate>4</Rate><review>We NEEDED to get away as a family and reconnect.  For once there was no itinerary - except to sleep.  There were four of us in the room with 2 double beds - not queen like the web page advertises (the sheets are even labeled 'double'). The room was amazingly large with a balcony you could walk out onto, have a seat and enjoy. The beds are always comfortable, but it would be nice if they were actually queen sized. It was great having a sink outside of the bathroom, especially with two girls.  We all slept through the housekeeping staffs shift, they did call to check on us and see if we needed anything.  Once we listed our needed they were very quick to fill the list.  Sweet & helpful staff, gorgeous grounds, fantastic room, good price and great sleep - thee best!!!!  Having a grocery store across the street was an added bonus!

The only problem we encountered was on the second night when we requested a microwave.  After an hour and a half I called again to check the status.  The man who answered the phone (night shift employee) said he had already spoke with us to let us know that all the microwaves were being used - he gave a sassy sorry and he hung up.  Funny, I was sitting by the phone the entire time and the room phone NEVER rang.  Ticked me off, but I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.< /review>< Pictures>

<userid>111277956594489958576<//userid><username>Christina Knoles</username>< Time>
1421451060096</Time>
<Rate>3<//Rate>< Review>
I cannot believe people rate this Double Tree as highly as I have seen.  The staff is nice, but this hotel is in very sad condition.   It is located near our son so we check each year to see if the "promised" renovations will ever be completed.  In 4 years, nothing yet, although they did upgrade the wifi.  I am told they have had a series of owners.  But how Hilton allows this property to keep its franchise is a mystery.  It is next to a small golf course so perhaps that is the reason.  But do not be fooled into thinking this is anything like a traditional Doubletree.  It isn't.  For example, when were were there last, the booths in the breakfast room looked as if someone had slashed them all with a knife and the stuffing was coming out in wads.  They have repaired that, according to the desk.  But nothing else other than the Wifi.  I would not recommend it as there are other properties better in the area.<//Review>

<user>103973464316630695956< /user><rating>3< /rating><Resp>None< /Resp><pictures>None< /pictures>< review>
This a very clean, separated from the main hotel, almost like a grouped units of building set next to the freeway 15. I really like the wide space inside and compfy beds for the weekend. But i was disappointed that there were EXTRA fees for "tourism fee, and SD assessement fee" from the hotel itself included since I booked it with Expedia. Expedia charged me a $10 fee that I am upset and not explained. All this adds up quite hefty. Plus, the hotel didn't offer me the free cookies I was looking forward to give my daughter. The walkway to our room was a steep hill. I had to use my wagon to haul my stuff. Yet there was a staff who offered to help pull my wagon and he was in a golfcart. There's a mini fridge and a tiny freezer that didn't work. No view for a patio, just a wall. Overall, it is okay. I wouldn't come back. Not for their hidden fees. Price was suppose to only be $107per night. You must ask for their ADDITIONAL hotel service fees FIRST! WHICH I didn't do.</review>

< text>
We stayed at this hotel for 6 nights in the past week and the experience was just amazing!

First, let me talk about why I booked this hotel in the first place. Originally I actually booked Marriott. After trying to call them to book a crib for my room for my baby and received extremely rude service over the phone (the person hung up on me after I questioned him about his rudeness over the phone), I cancelled my reservation with them and started looking elsewhere. Found this place on Expedia and the pictures looked amazing and the price was good so I booked it.

Property & Location:

The hotel is located right off Highway 15 and minutes away a shopping center with lots of shopping and restaurant options. The room is large and clean, very modern and nicely decorated. The only thing was our room only had a shower and no tub so it was a little difficult for us to bathe our two toddlers.

Service:

The staff is what made our trip unforgettable. Upon arrival, the front desk staff offered cookies and water to my two kids. They switched our room based on my needs and explained in detail where everything is located on the property. I was fully prepared to pay for the wireless internet but the lady waived the internet fee (we didn't end up getting charged anyway since we are HHonors members). Most importantly, seeing we have two young kids, the lady also gave us complimentary breakfast buffet vouchers for all 6 days that we stayed there!

Checking out was also extremely easy and efficient. I went to the front desk and provided my room number and it was all done. Although I have agreed to pay the $10/day parking, the front desk staff waived that for me as well!

Now onto our buffet breakfast service. The food selection was great with the traditional hot breakfast buffet and even smoked salmon. We were served by three different servers during our stay and all of them were quite pleasant and extremely attentive. They even remembered what we liked to drink after the first morning and brought our preferred drinks the next day. The only area of improvement in here is that the three servers all had different ideas on what's included in the complimentary breakfast voucher. The first server said we could order everything off of a la carte menu on top of the buffet. The next server said we are only allowed in the buffet and the third server said we can order off the menu but with limited selections. This was a little confusing but a minor problem since I only ate from the buffet anyway.

Overall, my family and I truly enjoyed the experience we had at Hotel Karlan and if we do ever go back to San Diego then that would be the hotel of choice.</text>

< Review>
I spent the night here after a wedding.  The hotel wasn't up to my doubletree standards.  I was kinda of expecting more in terms of the upkeep of the place and nicer amenities.

The person who helped me at the front desk was friendly however had difficulty finding me on their system.  She offered me warm cookies and water which was nice.

They didn't put me in the hilton honor floor which is the second and third floor; I was a bit disappointed at first but didn't think too much of it. I'm only a silver status so there wasn't much I was expecting. Wished they offered free breakfast and internet. There wasn't even a fridge or minibar when I came in. I ended up staying on the first floor. It was difficult to find my room; somewhat like a small maze. What was annoying was hearing the person upstairs walking loudly or the water being turned on. Later at 3 am,  there was a flock of birds at the golf course who could not keep quiet.< /Review>

<Rate>4</Rate>< Review>
I came here for business. Two people made a huge difference here... Richard, the fromt desk supervisor receptionist, and Nickolas (Niko) the server at the restaurant.

When my coworker and I checked in, I got a different lady who was a supervisor and my coworker got Richard, also a supervisor, as a receptionist. My receptionist didn't even give the same greeting "Hi! Welcome to DoubleTree Hilton! How can I help you today?"  whereas mine was "Can I help you?" in a unpleasant voice. At the end, she didn't even tell me the layout of the area nor helped me find the closest parking. As I walked to my coworker dealing with Richard, he asked if I knew where to park or was given information. I told him no, and he apologized on thr behalf of the other supervisor and helped finished her work for her. He then even gave me a cookie and said it was suppose to be a courtesy to all check-in (and the cookie was suoer good)! Later on, I didn't like my room (they were renovating) and I asked if Ibcould change to a different room closer to my coworker, and Richard didn't hesitate at all to do so! He was great!!!

As for Niko, he is such a beautiful soul, physically and spiritually! He was our waiter/server: his smile and attitude was so pleasant, beautiful, sweet, and kind! He was super down to earth, and just so sweet overall! He constantly checked up on us... and even though he knew we were talking about how great he is, he didn't even let that deterred him from delivering great customer service! He is also the room service guy. We actually initially saw him when we were getting out of the pool, lost like puppies, he told us where to go (as he was doing room service delivering food). His smile was just so contagious, and his laugh was pleasant to hear. He really made both me and my coworker want to be around him and dine in, which we did the last two nights we were there. Niko had to work on his birthday on April 27 too, so we felt bad he didn't get to be off... but that didn't change is wonderful attitude one bit! Great guy!

All in all, we both had a great stay because of these two. Now, if only the rest were as good as these two, it would have been a 5 star rating... these two gentleman made a difference!</Review>

< review>
We stayed at this location the beginning of august . Hearing it had been re done we expected it to be way nicer then it was . After calling three time to see if our room was ready we couldn't get a early check in and waited till 3 ( that is check in time so understandable ) when we arrived we were told that unfortunately they did not have the room we had a reservation for and the only thing they had was a double queen . Seriously! How do I have a reservation for something that you don't have ? Isn't that the point of a reservation ? I ask to speak to the manager. She went into the back to get the manager but instead of the manager coming out she came back and forth to the computer checking for a room.. Manager never came out! After waiting a couple min she magically found a room . The lady helping me had a attitude with me because I clearly was unset about the situation, when she found the room my credit card was in my hand and she snatched in out of my hand instead of asking for it. Rude and unprofessional! The third night our son was staying with us instead of with grandma and we ask for a rollaway bed . They brought a rollaway bed up and as soon as I was making up the bed I saw a bug , I thought it might be a bed bug but looking closer I realized it was not a bed bug but that there were three more bugs ( I freaked out ) We got rid of the bed but needless to say I didn't sleep much that night ! Just out of curiosity we checked the web site and they were still selling king bed rooms that they didn't have . Very miss leading! Won't ever stay here again!< /review>

NOT a quality Doubletree hotel. I booked through Priceline at a good price, the man who checked me in was nice but once I got to the room. The room was USED! The dresser drawers were flung open, there were USED towels on the bathroom floor, trash in the trashcan and used soap in the sink. I was already tired from hauling my luggage around trying to find my room... to then be told I'd be put in another room all the way on the other side of the hotel and I'd have to pick up the keys in the lobby. The front desk clerk apologized gave me the new keys and breakfast coupons for the inconvenience. In the new room a nasty bug falls on me while taking a shower üò† I rushed out in the morning to go to work and my boyfriend stayed behind. I call the hotel to be transferred to his room and a clerk named Daryl hangs up on me 3 times! I ask for a manager so I can complain and a girl gets on the phone and transfers me to the room without allowing me to speak with her. I had a long commute, I'm tired and very disturbed with the horrible service and upkeep of this well known hotel name. I have never experienced anything like this at any hotel! Oh and this morning as I passed the pool, the water was yellowish green! By far the worse stay ever. It's sad because it's a beautiful property and the rooms are very nice but the upkeep and maintenance is horrendous!< /review>

< text>
NOT a quality Doubletree hotel. I booked through Priceline at a good price, the man who checked me in was nice but once I got to the room. The room was USED! The dresser drawers were flung open, there were USED towels on the bathroom floor, trash in the trashcan and used soap in the sink. I was already tired from hauling my luggage around trying to find my room... to then be told I'd be put in another room all the way on the other side of the hotel and I'd have to pick up the keys in the lobby. The front desk clerk apologized gave me the new keys and breakfast coupons for the inconvenience. In the new room a nasty bug falls on me while taking a shower üò† I rushed out in the morning to go to work and my boyfriend stayed behind. I call the hotel to be transferred to his room and a clerk named Daryl hangs up on me 3 times! I ask for a manager so I can complain and a girl gets on the phone and transfers me to the room without allowing me to speak with her. I had a long commute, I'm tired and very disturbed with the horrible service and upkeep of this well known hotel name. I have never experienced anything like this at any hotel! Oh and this morning as I passed the pool, the water was yellowish green! By far the worse stay ever. It's sad because it's a beautiful property and the rooms are very nice but the upkeep and maintenance is horrendous!</text>
